author: mcombellack
msg: We should call e.toString() rather than e.getMessage() since some exceptions, such as NullPointerException, do not have a Messgae so return null. This then causes a NullPointerException to be thrown since you cannot pass null into the constructor of IOException. This then hides the original cause of the Exception
